    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="619"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/5529</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The British Embassy present their compliments to the Department of State and,
                    with reference to the Embassy’s memorandum of November 27th last, have the
                    honour to state that they are in receipt of a telegram from the Foreign Office
                    from which it appears that the Japanese representative at Peking has now been
                    instructed to give his full support to Allied representations to the Chinese
                    Government, urging that all enemy subjects should be deported.</p>
                <p>It would seem that such action on the part of the Chinese Government was more
                    necessary than ever in view of the possibility that the German and Austrian
                    prisoners in Siberia may be released by the Russian Bolshevist government, and
                    that there would thus be an influx of the former into China.</p>
                <p>The British Embassy are instructed to urge the United States Government to
                    request the United States Minister at Peking to join his Allied colleagues in
                    pressing the Chinese Government to adopt the principle of deportation of enemy
                    subjects.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 10, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
